The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Douglas rejects Md. Sp. offer

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: Mohammedan Sportings Brazilian defender Douglas da Silva on Thursday refused to accept the clubs offer of a reduced pay cheque. This means that he will not be seen in the clubs colours for the last three CFL Premier Division matches. 

We offered him half the salary, but as of now he hasnt got back with a positive answer, club secretary Sultan Ahmed said. 

It has been learnt that Douglas and coach Subhas Bhowmick met at a club officials residence but couldnt reach a solution. 




